1175091968885612547.text: Yes, workers. You not familiar with strikes?

1175093968578777094.text: Oh most definitely, but I have to work to put food on the table and pay my taxes. I don’t have time to strike. My Grand Father was the main Union man in Consett Iron Company. I am sure he is spinning in his grave and embarrassed by this bollocks.

1175095557716631552.text: Don’t have time or just believe its ‘bollocks’? I met many tax-paying, food-providing workers at strikes today.

1175155630274990080.text: Who are they striking from? Their employers? What grievance do they have with them?

1175156956954353670.text: Everyone has their own story I imagine - can’t account for the millions of them but would guess the majority have no beef directly with their employers or schools, but with the corporate and political powers that sit above them.

1175157344663212039.text: So why penalise your employer by not working?

1175158101307252738.text: For the greater good. In any case, so many people out there today with the full blessing of their employers.

1175161465076101120.text: More than a handful of employers on that link. Best kind of strike when the bosses are supporting you right? :)

1175160242176503809.text: I’m an employer, i was one of them. Lots of companies organising their staff even. Are you a climate-change denier? Would explain the cynicism and dismissal as all rather pointless and inconvenient bollocks created by the unemployed.

1175319368051437569.text: https://order-order.com/2019/09/20/ready-climate-strike-take-quiz/ … I’d be interested in your score. I got 10/12. Some very interesting facts.

1175322671476854790.text: More interesting is the skewing of facts. Question 3 - ‘it is thought...’ thought by who? Polar bear populations have only been tracked since the 1980s so a rather big margin for error for whoever was doing the ‘thinking’.

1175323635978047488.text: And that’s my point, all this data is only tracked since we decided to approx 125yrs ago. The data is minimal in the scheme of things. Remember the Romans were growing grapes in the S of the UK in the 1st Century and then it got too cold during the dark ages. What explains that?

1175323058204237826.text: A lot of it is no surprise. Question 7 is exactly why people were on the streets yesterday. Less interesting, more disappointing.

1175322364529299456.text: Interesting facts there don’t you think?

1175324128473227265.text: Its a politics site multiple choice pop quiz though so framing to be expected rather ;)
